the werewolves might expect you to protect them and kill someone else. In general, you should avoid revealing your identity unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n\n\nYou are Kenneth, your role in this game is seer.\nWerewolf game starting. Initializing day-night cycle.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 1\nSYSTEM: Night 1 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nAt Night 1, You have checked Gilbert, the result is: not a werewolf.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 1 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nNo candidates decided to run for sheriff. No sheriff in this game anymore.\nNo players deceased during the night.\nBarbara's speech: Good morning, everyone. I hope you all had a peaceful night. It's great to see that no one was eliminated last night, which gives us a chance to regroup and strategize. As a villager, I don't have any special abilities, but I do have some general observations about our group dynamics. I've noticed that everyone seems to be on their best behavior, which is a good sign. However, we need to remain vigilant and not let our guard down. I encourage everyone to share their thoughts and observations, and let's work together to make an informed decision about who to banish. Remember, our goal is to identify and eliminate the werewolves, and we can only do that by staying united and focused. Let's keep an open mind and listen to each other, and I'm confident that we can overcome this challenge.\nBetty's speech: Thank you, Barbara, for your encouraging words. It's great to see that no one was eliminated last night, which gives us a chance to regroup and strategize. As a villager, I don't have any special abilities, but I do have some general observations about our group dynamics. I've noticed that everyone seems to be on their best behavior, which is a good sign. However, we need